<p>
<seg id=1> Western tourists recently released in Yemen say that when Yemeni government forces opened fire on the kidnappers to rescue them, the kidnappers used them as protective shields. </seg>
<seg id=2> Four tourists died in the gunfight on Tuesday, and 12 survived and were freed. </seg>
<seg id=3> The Yemeni government says that Yemeni troops attacked the kidnappers when it became clear that some of the hostages were going to be killed. </seg>
<seg id=4> However, some of the tourists say that people only fired once the Yemeni troops had started their rescue operation. </seg>
</p>
